    },
    "founder-story": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Celine Beaumont began in a small studio in Toronto's Fashion District, with a simple idea: that everyday clothing should feel as considered as anything reserved for special occasions. Two decades later, that idea hasn't changed.</p><p>Every piece we make starts with a fabric we can stand behind — natural fibres, responsibly sourced, cut and sewn by a small team of pattern-makers and seamstresses we know by name. We keep our runs small on purpose: more care in every stitch, less waste in every collection, and clothing built to be worn for years, not seasons.</p><p>From our first dress to our latest collection, we've stayed close to home — designing, cutting and finishing everything right here in Toronto, for women across Canada who want their wardrobe to feel like them.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "full_width": false,
        "padding_top": 24,
        "padding_bottom": 56
      }
    },
